04:38.611 --> 04:43.700
You have this look of,
"What the heck have I got myself into?"

04:43.783 --> 04:45.702
-You're right.
-So, tell us about that that.

04:45.785 --> 04:48.621
No, you're right. That's a good read.

04:48.705 --> 04:52.125
I've owned it for two years.
And it's been vacant for two years.

04:52.208 --> 04:56.004
I spent a lot of time, money and energy
on it and it's not it's not rentable.

04:56.087 --> 04:58.881
And it's it's just been
kind of a cash drain.

04:58.965 --> 05:01.759
And coming from New York.
I don't seem to have the time.

05:01.843 --> 05:03.052
And you're not here full time.

05:03.136 --> 05:06.389
No. You know, I had some grand ideas
for a retail space downstairs

05:06.472 --> 05:07.515
and a residential upstairs.

05:07.598 --> 05:09.559
Of course, things change
when you run into issues.

05:09.642 --> 05:12.770
-What year is it exactly?
-I think 1789 is the foundation.

05:12.854 --> 05:15.565
-Wow.
-That's when Hudson was poppin'.

05:15.648 --> 05:19.068
It needs some help
and it needs to be rented.

05:19.152 --> 05:20.653
I have limited experience being a host.

05:20.737 --> 05:23.281
It's a ton of work and I don't know
if I can manage that

05:23.364 --> 05:27.660
because being in New York City
and having this house two hours away,

05:27.744 --> 05:29.746
I can't be managing
any kind of short-term rental.

05:29.829 --> 05:31.956
I really need Peter and Gen
to help me out

05:32.040 --> 05:34.500
and hopefully turn this place around
for me.

05:36.419 --> 05:38.463
-So this is it.
-Okay.

05:39.088 --> 05:42.884
It's definitely smaller
than I saw in the pictures,

05:42.967 --> 05:46.679
and there's nothing to work with.
No floors, no cabinets, nothing.

05:46.763 --> 05:52.018
You can see that it would lend well
to something of a storefront,

05:52.101 --> 05:53.853
maybe an art gallery
or something like that .

05:53.936 --> 05:55.271
Or a great vacation rental.

05:55.355 --> 05:58.024
Look, I know you were thinking
about this as retail,

05:58.107 --> 06:01.027
but as a businessman,
I see this as a potential place

06:01.110 --> 06:03.613
to have another sleeping area

06:03.696 --> 06:07.116
that could be rented separately
to the upstairs or in conjunction with.

06:07.200 --> 06:09.327
Like me, I have a family with three kids.

06:09.410 --> 06:10.912
I'd like to rent the whole space.

06:10.995 --> 06:13.331
Peter says let's make this
a short-term rental.

06:13.414 --> 06:16.793
And I don't see that right now
because it's such a small space.

06:16.876 --> 06:20.588
My vision was a retail space.
So, we'll see.

06:21.089 --> 06:25.676
I mean, this is great. Imagine if you were
a guest here and this becomes that.

06:25.760 --> 06:30.515
There's a dining room table all along
this long narrow corridor, right?

06:30.598 --> 06:33.393
You open up your windows,
you're eating with your family.

06:33.476 --> 06:37.772
People are walking by,
maybe have a few rocking chairs, whatever.

06:37.855 --> 06:40.191
I love this indoor-outdoor thing.

06:40.274 --> 06:43.736
This is a big marketing point,
a big selling point for this place.

06:43.820 --> 06:46.239
-Right. I love that.
-You've got a diamond here, mate.

06:46.322 --> 06:48.116
-Thank you so much.
-Yeah.

06:48.199 --> 06:50.576
-Let's go look at the upstairs unit.
-All right.

06:50.660 --> 06:52.412
-Let's do it.
-We're ready to do it.

06:54.747 --> 06:59.210
-This is really sweet.
-This is lovely.

06:59.752 --> 07:01.963
-Did you do all this?
-Yes.

07:02.046 --> 07:04.632
The majority of the money went
toward renovating this kitchen.

07:04.715 --> 07:07.468
Ample size kitchen.
It's a good open layout.

07:07.552 --> 07:11.931
Open to the rest of the room. You're not
holed-up in an old 1700s kitchen.

07:12.014 --> 07:15.893
So, there's two floors in this upper unit.
This floor and another upstairs, right?

07:15.977 --> 07:18.521
-Right. Yes, there's a third floor.
-Let's go.

07:18.604 --> 07:20.273
-Watch your head.
-Cute!

07:20.356 --> 07:22.775
-Okay.
-Don't be afraid to use the handrail here.

07:23.693 --> 07:27.363
So this is the first landing and what
could be a small guest room.

07:27.447 --> 07:30.867
-Okay.
-This space is amazing.

07:30.950 --> 07:34.579
It's a total blank canvas,
which is a designer's dream.

07:34.662 --> 07:37.206
I'm gonna turn this out.
This is so sweet.

07:37.290 --> 07:39.709
-It's a nice space--
-And the ceilings are so high,

07:39.792 --> 07:42.795
but this rosette is beckoning,
it's still--

07:44.422 --> 07:45.673
-Sure.
-That's lovely.

07:45.756 --> 07:48.759
If you wanna poke your head out
and shout to your friend from the street.

07:48.843 --> 07:53.306
This is where, I guess, the hay was
downstairs from the carriage house, right?

07:53.389 --> 07:58.060
I suppose. I wasn't around then,
so I don't know what was happening.

07:58.144 --> 08:01.772
-I love this! This was money too.
-Oh, yeah. Absolutely.

08:01.856 --> 08:04.358
So, the third floor,
I've put some money into that as well.

08:04.442 --> 08:06.694
I had to meet code
with the sprinkler system.

08:06.777 --> 08:09.238
I put skylights in there
in an egressible window.

08:09.322 --> 08:11.866
And it shows a lot of light,
it's really beautiful.

08:11.949 --> 08:16.662
I know that all of this stuff
that's hidden away costs a packet.

08:16.746 --> 08:19.207
But you have not wasted money doing this.

08:19.290 --> 08:21.542
No, you're right.
And I need to recognize that.

08:21.626 --> 08:25.046
And you guys are inspiring me,
so this is something that,

08:25.129 --> 08:28.299
even though I spent
so much money on it, I think--

08:28.382 --> 08:31.552
-You want to make it work.
-Yeah. And I need some help. Clearly.

08:31.636 --> 08:33.011
Let's get down to business.

08:35.932 --> 08:38.100
-Okay.
-Talk to me.

08:38.183 --> 08:40.727
How much were you hoping to make?
What are your goals?

08:40.811 --> 08:46.442
Well, ultimately, I'd like to recoup
all of the renovation expense.

08:46.526 --> 08:50.571
I was originally thinking that I would
rent it as retail downstairs,

08:50.655 --> 08:52.198
-residential upstairs.
-Yeah.

08:52.281 --> 08:57.036
I figured that I could get
$1,500 downstairs, and potentially,

08:57.119 --> 08:59.622
$2,000, that might be aggressive,
for the upstairs.

08:59.705 --> 09:01.165
So, $3,500 a month.

09:01.249 --> 09:05.545
This place is costing me money every
single month that it sits here.

09:05.628 --> 09:08.839
I need to figure out how I can make
as much money as I possibly can.

09:08.923 --> 09:12.718
When it comes to short-term rentals,
think of it like three legs on a stool.

09:12.802 --> 09:14.053
You've got marketing,

09:14.554 --> 09:17.682
you've got operations
and you've got experiences, right?

09:17.765 --> 09:18.933
It's like owning a hotel.

09:19.016 --> 09:22.103
You need to get into the mindset of--
You're a general manager

09:22.186 --> 09:24.605
-of your own small boutique hotel.
-Yeah.

09:24.689 --> 09:28.401
So, I still think you can make more money
if you change the retail space

09:28.484 --> 09:30.403
into a short-term rental space.

09:30.486 --> 09:32.738
Your competition,
your "comps" as we call it,

09:32.822 --> 09:37.493
within five miles of you,
there are 199 properties.

09:37.577 --> 09:40.871
And the average nightly rate
is about 200 bucks.

09:40.955 --> 09:43.457
The difference with your places,

09:43.541 --> 09:46.419
if you rent out the upper unit,
I think, with certainty,

09:46.502 --> 09:49.463
-you could get $250 a night, okay?
-Okay.

09:49.547 --> 09:52.675
And then if you change the retail space
into a vacation rental,

09:52.758 --> 09:55.886
I think you'll get
about $150 a night for it.

09:56.429 --> 09:59.098
So that's $400 a night.

09:59.181 --> 10:02.101
The average occupancy rate
in Hudson is 48%

10:02.184 --> 10:04.729
That's about 15 nights per month.

10:04.812 --> 10:10.818
So, $400 times 15 is $6,000
or $72,000 a year.

10:10.901 --> 10:14.530
If I can get $6,000 a month,
that's way more than I expected to make,

10:14.614 --> 10:16.741
and it would help me
chip away at a lot of the costs

10:16.824 --> 10:18.576
I put into it over the past two years.

10:18.993 --> 10:22.038
If this was my property,
I would be so confident in it.

10:22.622 --> 10:25.833
So, will you let us change your
retail space into a short-term rental?

10:30.087 --> 10:32.798
-Go for it, yeah.
-All right, good. I feel better.

10:43.351 --> 10:46.854
We're launching our business plan,
and since this is Alex's first time,

10:46.937 --> 10:51.484
we have to teach him the basics,
or the 101 of short-term rental.

10:51.567 --> 10:54.528
we need to execute
a unique design that will help

10:54.612 --> 10:56.947
distinguish his property from all
the other rentals,

10:57.031 --> 10:59.700
and pull it off at a price
that Alex can afford.

11:00.076 --> 11:04.038
Next, we'll show Alex how to create
a website to promote his new listing.

11:04.622 --> 11:07.583
We'll also help find someone
to host his property.

11:07.667 --> 11:11.504
