11:33.776 --> 11:38.989
This whole back area, I want to extend
the bathroom so we have a full bathroom,

11:39.073 --> 11:41.409
yeah, with shower into kitchenette.

11:41.492 --> 11:44.161
Then we have this back wall
which was retail.

11:44.245 --> 11:47.832
I need this to be the destination
that seduces you in from the street.

11:47.915 --> 11:49.709
This is where we know
it's a carriage house.

11:49.792 --> 11:51.043
Where does the bed go?

11:51.127 --> 11:53.754
-This is my bedroom, living room area.
-Okay.

11:53.838 --> 11:57.550
Very much a studio apartment,
where kitchen and sleeping and lounging

11:57.633 --> 11:58.884
are all in one space.

11:58.968 --> 12:02.847
I'm trying to imagine how you'll fit,
but you're the expert.

12:02.930 --> 12:06.267
The furniture budget is another budget
that we really haven't talked about.

12:06.350 --> 12:09.478
And we have a lot of house to furnish,
so I know you're already

12:09.562 --> 12:11.397
super overly invested in this house.

12:11.480 --> 12:14.442
So I'd like to keep that budget
as small as possible.

12:14.525 --> 12:15.901
So let's look at we already have

12:15.985 --> 12:18.821
